                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.112 M22/20.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following from Carothers, Gomez Palacio, 26th instant: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Have just received following telegram from General Villa stating that he
                            has telegraphed directly to the several generals in Sonora giving them
                            positive orders to give full and complete guaranty to all foreigners in
                            that State, and that they may not be molested or cause them any
                            difficulties. Carothers.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
